### 🤖 Claude

Created a whitelist-style `.gitignore` at the repo root. It ignores everything by default, then explicitly re-includes:

```
# Ignore everything by default
*

# Re-include the presentation folder and all its contents
!presentation/
!presentation/**

# Re-include the README
!README.md

# Re-include this file itself
!.gitignore
```

This means only `presentation/`, `README.md`, and `.gitignore` itself will ever be tracked — anything else added to the repo root (build artifacts, temp files, credentials, etc.) will be ignored automatically.

