### 🤖 Claude

Created the `Azure Infrastructure/` folder with a complete Bicep landing zone and a GitHub Actions deployment pipeline. Also updated `.gitignore` to include the new folders.

**New folder structure:**

```
Azure Infrastructure/
├── main.bicep                  # Root orchestration (subscription scope)
├── modules/
│   ├── logAnalytics.bicep      # Log Analytics Workspace
│   ├── network.bicep           # VNet + 3 subnets (app, data, mgmt)
│   ├── storageAccount.bicep    # Hardened Storage Account (no public access, HTTPS only, soft-delete)
│   └── keyVault.bicep          # Key Vault (RBAC, purge-protected, diagnostic logging)
├── parameters/
│   ├── dev.parameters.json     # Dev environment values
│   └── prod.parameters.json    # Prod environment values
└── README.md                   # Setup guide + local dev commands

.github/
└── workflows/
    └── deploy-azure-infra.yml  # GitHub Actions pipeline
```

**Pipeline behaviour:**
- **Pull Request** → lint + validate + what-if only (no deployment)
- **Push to main** → lint → validate → what-if → deploy to dev
- **Manual trigger** → choose environment (dev/prod) and region

**Authentication:** OIDC (federated identity) — no stored Azure credentials in GitHub secrets

**Updated `.gitignore`** to whitelist `Azure Infrastructure/` and `.github/` alongside the existing `presentation/` and `README.md`.

